eeksforgeeks.org/python/substitution-cipher/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noop=
ener"><span>substitution cipher</span></a><span>, where each letter in the =
plaintext is replaced by a letter some fixed number of positions down the a=
lphabet.</span></li><li value=3D"2"><b><strong>Fixed key:</strong></b><span=
> The Caesar cipher uses a fixed key, which is the number of positions by w=
hich the letters are shifted. This key is known to both the sender and the =
receiver.</span></li><li value=3D"3"><b><strong>Symmetric encryption:</stro=
ng></b><span> The Caesar cipher is a </span><a href=3D"https://www.geeksfor=
